# Stellar / Soroban Reference

Use `external/stellar-ai-guide/` as the **primary reference** for all Stellar and Soroban related implementations in this project.

## Reference structure

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Starter_Prompts.md` | Protocol context, wallet-vs-dApp distinction, prompt templates |
| `Free_AI_Setup.md` | Free AI tooling setup (FreeLLMAPI, Freebuff, OpenRouter, Groq, Ollama) |
| `Claude_Code_Guide.md` | Claude Code commands, parallel agents, browser automation |
| `Recommended_AI_Tools.md` | Curated Stellar / AI tool ecosystem map |
| `countries/mx/` | Mexico-specific rails (SPEI, CETES, AlfredPay, BlindPay, Etherfuse) |
| `countries/br/` | Brazil-specific rails (PIX, TESOURO, BRZ, Transfero) |

## Rules

- Before implementing any Stellar/Soroban feature, consult the relevant guide files in `external/stellar-ai-guide/`.
- Use `Starter_Prompts.md` for protocol context and correct terminology.
- Follow patterns and best practices described in the guide over generic knowledge.
- For country-specific anchor/rail integrations, reference the appropriate `countries/<code>/` folder.
